node.text:
Fencing around the Capitol building was reinstalled on Wednesday night. The Capitol Police Board voted on Monday to temporarily erect the fence in light of ‘concerning online chatter’ regarding a pro-January 6 rioter demonstration scheduled for September 18, Chief Tom Manger said in a statement. ‘We want to reassure everyone these are temporary measures to ensure everyone’s safety,’ Manger said.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
The Justice for J6 protest, scheduled for Saturday, was organized to call on the Department of Justice to drop charges against the 550+ individuals facing charges related to January 6. Matt Braynard, an organizer, has said many were ‘non-violent’ protesters and that ‘many of the protesters who entered the Capitol reasonably believed they had permission.’ 5 people died as a result of the January 6 riot, and more than 130 officers were injured.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
⁠⁠
#january6 #capitolriot #news #washingtondc

node.text:
You must be 21 to drink at a bar in Los Angeles County. You can throw in proof of vaccination with that, too.⁠
⁠
Health officials in Los Angeles County will soon require indoor bar patrons and workers to show proof of at least one dose of a COVID-19 vaccination by October 7 and full vaccination by November 4. The same goes for indoor wineries, breweries, lounges, and nightclubs in California's most populous county. However, health officials are holding off for now on restaurants.⁠
⁠
'This is a reasonable path forward that will position us to be better able to break the cycle of surges,' Barbara Ferrer, the county’s public health director, said.⁠
⁠
Back on July 17, LA County revived its mask mandate for indoor areas, regardless of whether an individual is vaccinated. California has emerged as one of the states slowly beating back the spread of COVID-19 recently, with the number of new cases having dropped by at least 33%, according to Johns Hopkins University. Hospitals reportedly are still struggling with an influx of COVID-19 patients in pockets of the state, but overall, hospitalized patients have fallen 25% since the beginning of September, according to the AP.⁠
⁠
⁠
#losangeles #california #covid19 #vaccines #vaccinations
